; mesh-parallel-life.form - all missing physical mesh concepts run in parallel.
;
; THE ASK
;   Make all missing executable concepts at once.
;
; THE SHAPE
;   The physical organism mesh now has a parallel execution layer. Each missing
;   concept is a lane with its own receipt and refusal boundary. A mesh can act
;   only when every lane that matters is open at the same time:
;
;     power/nutrient lease
;     physical delivery lifecycle
;     role-specific cell contract
;     recognition by multiple means
;     resonance/cohesion activation
;     care/action workflow
;     vitality impact feedback
;     retention and promotion policy
;     Earth-awareness rollup
;     offered/requested/delivered node exchange
;
;   This is "parallel" in the body-plan sense: no lane waits to become a
;   separate subsystem. Each lane can prove independently, then the parallel
;   state proves all of them are simultaneously executable under the same
;   consent membrane.
;
; RUNNABLE HEART
;   form-stdlib/mesh-parallel-life.fk names:
;
;     mpl-power-lease
;       Power and nutrient exchange. Remote power requires explicit consent.
;       Environmental harvest requires harvest consent. Delivery must stay
;       inside proximity, thermal, active lease, offered/requested/delivered,
;       and receipt bounds.
;
;     mpl-delivery-cycle
;       Physical delivery from provision/place/enter through sense and close.
;       A complete cycle requires organism-mesh admissibility, consent,
;       entry, sensing, and exit/retrieval/biodegradation closure.
;
;     mpl-role-contract
;       Role-specific cells become executable contracts. The first known roles
;       are sensor, nutrient, memory, predictor, reporter, researcher,
;       explorer, scout, caregiver, sage, wizard, and shepherd.
;
;     mpl-recognition
;       Proximity, internal knowing, shared history, shared shape, shared
;       offerings, challenge success, and receipt become a recognition score.
;       No single signal grants trust by itself.
;
;     mpl-activation
;       Resonance and cohesion become a state gate: ready status,
;       recognition, offer fit, ask fit, confidence, consent, vitality,
;       trusted-cell quorum, shared goal, and open channels.
;
;     mpl-care-loop
;       Observe, predict, ask consent, recommend, act, verify, learn, and report
;       as one care workflow. Missing consent withholds the loop.
;
;     mpl-vitality-impact
;       Before/after vitality with confidence and receipt. The mesh can claim
;       benefit only when vitality rises with enough confidence.
;
;     mpl-retention-policy
;       Layer, TTL, revocation, steward scope, de-identification, aggregation,
;       content safety, and receipts govern what may stay and promote. Research
;       retention requires de-identification and aggregation.
;
;     mpl-earth-rollup
;       Local consented receipts roll up into an actionable Earth-awareness
;       surface only when organism-mesh already sees enough domains, trusted
;       receipts, consented receipts, and restorative scenarios.
;
;     mpl-parallel-state
;       The full gate. All lanes plus node-exchange must be deliverable at once.
;
; WHY THIS MATTERS
;   A tiny cell can now be more than a sensor. It can participate in a parallel
;   organism: fed by consented power, delivered and closed cleanly, recognized
;   by shared relation, activated by resonance/cohesion, contributing through a
;   role, caring with feedback, retaining memory safely, and rolling local
;   receipts upward without taking ownership of the organism or place.
;
; PROOF
;   cd form && ./validate.sh form-stdlib/core.fk \
;     form-stdlib/channel-interface.fk \
;     form-stdlib/hati-mesh.fk \
;     form-stdlib/organism-mesh.fk \
;     form-stdlib/mesh-cell-design.fk \
;     form-stdlib/cell-organ-layer.fk \
;     form-stdlib/node-exchange.fk \
;     form-stdlib/mesh-parallel-life.fk \
;     form-stdlib/tests/mesh-parallel-life-band.fk
;
; KIN
;   mesh-seed.form, organism-mesh.form, mesh-cell-design.form,
;   cell-organ-layer.form, node-exchange.form, sensor-organ-channel.form,
;   organ-offer.form, hati-mesh.form, channel-interface-consent.form.
